thread.title_full: MLB playoffs: New York Mets march on after beating Los Angeles Dodgers

author: The Sydney Morning Herald
title: MLB playoffs: New York Mets march on after beating Los Angeles Dodgers
text:
Daniel Murphy of the Mets reacts hits a solo home run in the sixth inning against the Dodgers. Photo: Getty Images
LOS ANGELES: The New York Mets have advanced to Major League Baseball's National League Championship Series by winning 3-2 at the Los Angeles Dodgers in the decisive game on Thursday, with Daniel Murphy responsible for the tying and go-ahead runs.
The Mets will play the Chicago Cubs in the NLCS.
New York trailed 2-1 when the Dodgers somehow failed to have anyone on third base during a play, and Murphy stole it, and then scored on a sacrifice fly. Murphy then hit a solo homer in the sixth to put the Mets ahead.
Closing pitcher Jeurys Familia made the first six-out save of his career as he worked the eighth and ninth in quick time.
Advertisement The big-spending Dodgers remain without a World Series title since 1988.
AP
